Sure, here are some examples:

1. *Posetu* smo dogovorili za sutra ujutru. (*We arranged a visit* for tomorrow morning.)
2. Prošle nedelje sam imao *posetu* od starih prijatelja. (Last week, I had *a visit* from old friends.)
3. Izvinite, ali ne primamo *posete* posle 18h. (Sorry, but we don't accept *visits* after 6pm.)
4. Nisam imao vremena da organizujem *posetu* rođacima u drugom gradu. (I didn't have time to arrange *a visit* to relatives in another city.)
5. Danas smo dobili *posetu* od predstavnika firme koja nam nudi usluge. (Today, we had *a visit* from a company representative offering us services.)
6. Moja *poseta* roditeljima trajala je tri dana. (My *visit* to my parents lasted three days.)
7. Nadam se da će mi *poseta* bolnici pomoći da se oporavim. (I hope that *the hospital visit* will help me recover.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "poseta" can be used both as a noun and a verb, and it can have different forms depending on the context and the tense.